  "comment": "IP Pixel Controller is an IP65-rated controller for the IP Pixelstrip 40 and IP Pixelstrip 80. Each of its four outputs can control up to 4 metres of any mixed setup of IP Pixelstrips, for a maximum total of 16 metres. It accepts DMX, Art-Net, sACN and Klingnet protocols.When using Art-Net or sACN, the controller can address every single RGB LED in each 4 m string, requiring up to 3840 channels / 8 DMX universes. The integrated section control modes enable users to easily group pixels to reduce the required number of DMX channels. It also offers a 8- and 12-channel control modes for smaller stage setups.The supported Kling-Net protocol allows easy control via the arKaos software. The controller also offers Stand-alone operation with Master/Slave, Manual modes and built-in programs.Dedicated cables carry both power and data signals from the controller to the IP Pixelstrips. A Power Pro True cable is included, as well as a quicklock bracket for easy installation. Its IP65 rating protects against dust and moisture for harsh environments such as temporary outdoor use.",
